      "text": "\n\n<table border=1 style='margin: auto; word-wrap: break-word;'><tr><td style='text-align: center; word-wrap: break-word;'>Grade: 1</td><td style='text-align: center; word-wrap: break-word;'>Subject: English Grammar</td><td style='text-align: center; word-wrap: break-word;'>Topic: Adjectives</td></tr></table>\n\n#####  $ \\underline{\\text{Reading}} $  $ \\underline{\\text{Material}} $:\n\nDescribing words (Adjectives): An adjective is a word that is used to describe something about a noun. They are also called describing words.\n\nExample: soft, warm, dry, big, tall, small, beautiful, funny, etc.\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"imgs/img_in_image_box_173_418_499_949.jpg\" alt=\"Image\" width=\"27%\" /></div>\n\n\nRolo is a  $ \\underline{\\text{funny}} $ clown.\n\nThe  $ \\underline{black} $ dog jumped over the bar.\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"imgs/img_in_image_box_643_1061_1098_1462.jpg\" alt=\"Image\" width=\"38%\" /></div>\n\n\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"><img src=\"imgs/img_in_image_box_261_1434_488_1616.jpg\" alt=\"Image\" width=\"19%\" /></div>\n",
